videos.headline: Mark Wood to Sakariya, out Caught by Krunal Pandya!! Five-wicket haul for Mark Wood! Mark Wood goes and quick and Sakariya miscues his pull towards mid-wicket. Taken by Krunal Pandya and DC are nine down. What a special spell this has been by Wood. Superb! Sakariya c Krunal Pandya b Mark Wood 4(4) [4s-1]

Mark Wood to Axar, out Caught by (sub)Prerak Mankad !! On the batter's pads and Axar flicks it straight to the fielder at deep square leg. That's wicket no. 4 for Mark Wood tonight. Can he get a five-wicket haul? Axar c (sub)Prerak Mankad b Mark Wood 16(11) [4s-1 6s-1]

Avesh Khan to Warner, out Caught by Gowtham! End of Warner's fight. A slower delivery by Avesh Khan and Warner gets completely outfoxed due to the lack of pace. Swings across, but miscues it completely. Gowtham at long-on settles underneat it and completes a pretty safe catch. Reverse cups it and LSG are inching close to an emphatic win. Warner c Gowtham b Avesh Khan 56(48) [4s-7]

Avesh Khan to Aman Hakim Khan, out Caught by Pooran!! That's that from Aman Khan! LSG continue to hold their command on this match. Avesh Khan goes short and quick as the batter gets hurried up due to the pace and bounce. Goes for a nothing shot, a half hearted pull and the top edge balloons straight up in the air. Pooran settles underneath it and completes a safe catch. Aman Hakim Khan c Pooran b Avesh Khan 4(5)

Ravi Bishnoi to Powell, out Lbw!! Another one bites the dust. No need to review that. As plumb as it could get. Was a googly by Ravi Bishnoi and it kept a touch low too. Powell gets beaten and rapped on the pads. Ravi Bishnoi appeals and the umpire wastes no time to raise that dreaded finger. This game is fairly one sided at the moment. Powell lbw b Ravi Bishnoi 1(3)

Ravi Bishnoi to Rossouw, out Caught by Mayers!! Review for an lbw taken - or wait, it's for a catch! Looked out - lbw, but the ball deflected on to the bat. Hit the back of his willow and flew straight to Mayers who takes it behind the keeper. Rossouw knew there was bat involved, hence he starts walking back to the pavilion, without waiting for the replays to confirm it. Pretty strange dismissal to be honest. Rossouw c Mayers b Ravi Bishnoi 30(20) [4s-3 6s-1]

Mark Wood to Sarfaraz Khan, out Caught by Gowtham at fine leg!! Mark Wood gets a 3-fer! He is ruling the roost at home. A well-directed short ball and it angles in too, cramping Sarfaraz Khan for room. He arches back and tries to ramp it over the keeper but only manages to get it towards fine leg. It's straight down the throat of Gowtham and he makes no mistake. DC are in some trouble now. Sarfaraz Khan c Gowtham b Mark Wood 4(9) [4s-1]

Mark Wood to Mitchell Marsh, out Bowled!! Oh, my word! Absolutely sensational! Mitchell Marsh departs for a golden duck! Look at the joy on Mark Wood's face. He takes off in celebration. This one is a bit more fuller than the previous one as this one pitches outside off. Mitchell Marsh goes for a drive down the ground but the jags back in sharply to go past the inside edge and rattle the stumps. Mark Wood is on a hat-trick next ball. Mitchell Marsh b Mark Wood 0(1)

Mark Wood to Prithvi Shaw, out Bowled!! That's what raw pace can do and Mark Wood is cok-a-hoop! He steams in and bowls a fuller length ball at 147.3kph in the tight off-stump channel. Prithvi Shaw goes for an expansive drive with minimal front foot movement. The ball seams in a bit as well and the big gap between his bat and pads means the ball crashes into the stumps. Prithvi Shaw b Mark Wood 12(9) [4s-2]

Sakariya to Ayush Badoni, out Caught by Sarfaraz Khan!! Ayush Badoni premeditates and shuffles across. Sakariya does well to follow him with an off-cutter. He tries to scoop it over the keeper but gets it high on the bat. Sarfaraz Khan moves to his left and pouches it safely. Ayush Badoni c Sarfaraz Khan b Sakariya 18(7) [4s-1 6s-2]

Khaleel Ahmed to Pooran, out Caught by Prithvi Shaw!! A blazing cameo from Pooran comes to an end! Full ball outside off, it was there to be hit and Pooran brings out an expansive cover drive. However, he has hit it straight to Shaw. He is standing at the edge of the circle at extra cover and takes it nicely. Pooran c Prithvi Shaw b Khaleel Ahmed 36(21) [4s-2 6s-3]

Khaleel Ahmed to Stoinis, out Caught by Sarfaraz Khan!! Khaleel Ahmed strikes! That will definitely make him feel better as Mayers made DC pay after he had dropped him early. Good length ball outside off, slanting across Stoinis with some extra bounce. Loose from Stoinis as he goes chasing after it with a cut shot but only manages an edge behind. Sarfaraz Khan behind the stumps takes a regulation catch. A good phase of play for DC this. Stoinis c Sarfaraz Khan b Khaleel Ahmed 12(10) [6s-1]

Axar to Mayers, out Bowled!! That has turned square from outside off - an absolute ripper from Axar who belts out a big roar after getting the dangerous Mayers. This is fired in from round the wicket, lands on a length outside off, Mayers looks to cut but it turns in sharply off the bald patch. Goes right through the gate and knocks over off stump, bringing an end to a blistering knock..Mayers b Axar 73(38) [4s-2 6s-7]

Kuldeep Yadav to Hooda, out Caught by Warner!! It's not the wicket they want, but Kuldeep breaks the partnership! Nicely tossed up googly outside off, dips on Hooda who doesn't quite go through with the lofted shot. Perhaps that's a result of not being to the pitch of it. He chips it high in the air, and Warner takes a good catch moving to his left at long-off. The partnership was worth 79, of which Hooda only contributed 17. Hooda c Warner b Kuldeep Yadav 17(18)

Sakariya to Rahul, out Caught by Axar!! Sakariya continues his good record against Rahul! Has got him out four times in four innings! Slower length ball on leg, Rahul whips it in the air, doesn't get hold of it and it's straight to Axar Patel. Catching practice for him at deep backward square. Rahul c Axar b Sakariya 8(12) [6s-1]
